# Environment Variables Template

## Frontend Environment Variables
Copy to `.env.local` in project root

```env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
VITE_API_BASE=/api

# For production deployment
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.railway.app
# VITE_API_BASE=/api
```

## Backend Environment Variables
Copy to `webmak/.env`

```env
# Django Settings
DEBUG=True
SECRET_KEY=django-insecure-your-secret-key-here-change-in-production

# Database
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///db.sqlite3
# For production: DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:port/dbname

# Allowed Hosts
ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1
# For production: ALLOWED_HOSTS=your-domain.com,www.your-domain.com

# CORS Configuration
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://localhost:3000
# For production: CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend.vercel.app

# JWT Tokens
JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_LIFETIME=900  # 15 minutes in seconds
JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_LIFETIME=604800  # 7 days in seconds

# Email (if implementing email features)
EMAIL_BACKEND=django.core.mail.backends.console.EmailBackend
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USE_TLS=True
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-app-password

# Security (for production)
SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=False
SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=False
CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE=False
# For production, set all to True
```

---

## 🚀 Deployment Environment Variables

### Vercel (Frontend)
Set these in Vercel project settings:

```
VITE_API_URL=https://your-railway-backend.railway.app
VITE_API_BASE=/api
```

### Railway (Backend)
Set these in Railway project settings:

```
DEBUG=False
SECRET_KEY=your-super-secure-random-key-here
ALLOWED_HOSTS=your-railway-app.railway.app
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:port/dbname
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-vercel-frontend.vercel.app
SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=True
SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=True
CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE=True
```

---

## 📝 Notes

- Never commit `.env` files to Git
- Use `.gitignore` to exclude environment files
- For production, use strong SECRET_KEY values
- Keep CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS specific to your domains
- Regenerate SECRET_KEY for each production deployment
